{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4a3c52e1-2ac2-4ac5-9922-f0b82dc0fb5b","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Install the .NET 11 SDK** on your dev machine and CI from [dot.net](https://dot.net).\n\n**5. Update NuGet packages** — run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` packages for major-version bumps and check the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) doc for anything that affects your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"29f8f7f6-707b-413a-8308-e982a0457a0d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":332,"requestId":"E02F:115522:7797122:8447B8A:69F406BC"},"id":"b81d636a-87bb-4bf1-9d80-561c62e83cef","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:49:57.119Z","parentId":"4adae227-7bf4-4bc6-922b-3f3e43f81149"}
